  "content_id": "be125000-2077-4497-95a7-cd69059201a9",
  "description": "Tax and reporting rules for employers allowing private use of heavy goods vehicles by employees",
  "details": {
    "body": "<p>As an employer, if you let an employee borrow a heavy goods vehicle (<abbr title=\"Heavy goods vehicle\">HGV</abbr>) for private use it doesn’t count as a taxable expense or benefit – as long as the vehicle is mostly used for work purposes.</p>\n\n<p>This means:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you don’t have to report it to <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>\n</li>\n  <li>you don’t deduct or pay tax or National Insurance on it</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"salary-sacrifice-arrangements\">Salary sacrifice arrangements</h2>\n\n<p>If you let an employee borrow an <abbr title=\"Heavy goods vehicle\">HGV</abbr> as part of a salary sacrifice arrangement it won’t be exempt. You’ll need to report on <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/employer-reporting-expenses-benefits/reporting-and-paying\">form P11D</a> whichever amount is higher:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the salary given up</li>\n  <li>the annual value of the use of the <abbr title=\"Heavy goods vehicle\">HGV</abbr> - this includes rent, hire charges and any other related expenses</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>These rules don’t apply to arrangements made before 6 April 2017 - check <a href=\"/guidance/salary-sacrifice-and-the-effects-on-paye\">when the rules will change</a>.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"technical-guidelines\">Technical guidelines</h2>\n\n<p>The following guide contains more detailed information:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/eimanual/EIM22990.htm\">heavy goods vehicles: exemption</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n",
    "external_related_links": [

    ]
  },
